  "prompt": "What does \"net 30\" mean vs. \"due in 30 days\"?",
  "response": "\"Net 30\" and \"due in 30 days\" are essentially the same thing in business invoicing and payment terms. Both phrases indicate that the full payment for an invoice is expected within 30 calendar days from the invoice date. \n\nSome slight nuances:\n- \"Net 30\" is more commonly used in professional invoicing\n- Both mean the entire balance is due within 30 days\n- Neither implies partial payments or installments\n- The 30-day period typically starts from the invoice date\n\nIn practice, they are functionally identical payment terms.",
